Harmony Holdings Inc. said today that the Capital Media Group and Unimedia S.A. had signed a letter of intent to acquire Harmony for about $21 million in cash and stock. The purchase price is $3.50 a share, Harmony said. Harmony shareholders will receive one-third in cash and two-thirds in Capital Media common stock at the average closing price for the five trading days before the date of shareholder approval, the company said. Harmony's stock rose 6.25 cents today, to $2.5625. Harmony is a Los Angeles-based television commercial and music video production company with production offices in Los Angeles and New York.